  "text": "Can you tell me what bias creates their momentum toward the chosen path of service to self. I am Ra. We can speak only in metaphor. Some love the light. Some love the darkness. It is a matter of the unique and infinitely various creator, a choosing and a playing among its experiences as a child upon a picnic. Some enjoy the picnic and find the sun a beautiful, the food a delicious, the games refreshing, and glow with the joy of creation. Some find the night a delicious, their picnic, a being a pain, a difficulty, the sufferings of others, and the examination of the perversities of nature. These enjoy a different picnic. All these experiences are available. It is free will of each entity which chooses the form of play, the form of pleasure.",
